<HEADER>
A7197 &Cx1f; ttc-z
u v BC-LADN-BUDGET &LR;      08-14 0169
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, Aug. 15 and thereafter. For questions about stories, please
contact Stew Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   IRON-GIANT (Los Angeles) _ What in the world happened to the
``Iron Giant''? Despite universally positive reviews of the Warner
Bros. animated movie, the ``Iron Giant'' opened with a massive thud
last weekend. It finished with $5.7 million at 2,171 theaters _
barely one-fifth of the business generated by Bruce Willis' ``Sixth
Sense.'' That's a flat-out disaster for a project that racked up a
tab estimated at $50 million and an embarrassment for the studio
considering ``Iron Giant'' debut during a supercharged summer in
which grosses have risen an astounding 20 percent over last year's
record-setting pace. By Dave McNary. (Will move in the ``e''
entertainment and ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   X X X &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
