   WITH
</P>
<P>
   ADOPT-MIXED _ DAYTON, Ohio _ White couples who adopt Asian
children face a philosophical struggle. Some parents say their
daughters will be All-American, just like them. Other parents
believe teaching their children about their heritage will prepare
them for racism they surely will face as minorities in America.
Often, even husband and wife don't agree on which strategy makes
sense. (Lee, Dayton Daily News) MOVED
