   ADOPT-AGENCY _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Carefully choosing an adoption
agency is an important step in the process. (Lee, Dayton Daily
News) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   ROADSTUDY _ North Carolina and South Carolina are the only two
Southern states that keep tabs on the odd phenomenon of people
``killed while lying in the road,'' and North Carolina has begun a
formal study of the issue. Especially common during the summer, the
incidents typically happen on either side of midnight and often
involve intoxicated victims who apparently like the idea of
sleeping on the warm pavement. (Burritt, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MEMPHMAYOR _ MEMPHIS _ Jim ``The King'' Lawler, a wrestling
announcer whose TV line to women is ``show us your puppies,'' is
running, and so is former cart-wheeling Georgia Tech football coach
Pepper Rodgers. But there are also two serious candidates for mayor
of Memphis, a city that only recently elected its first
African-American mayor. A look at the very weird race to run the
South's most famous river town. (Koingsmark, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   ROADEAD _ ASHEBORO, N.C. _ Late one Friday night, trucker Levy
Giles spotted a car parked on the right shoulder of U.S. 220, so he
moved into the left-hand lane. Unknown to him, the car's two
occupants were lying in the highway. The tractor-trailer ran over
them, adding two more victims to a peculiar category of North
Carolina's highway deaths: killed while lying in the road. But the
deaths of longtime sweethearts Tina Armstrong and Deon Ledbetter
remain a mystery and have become a major controversy involving
allegations of drug abuse, brutality and racial discrimination. A
detailed account of the incident and the aftermath. (Burritt,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BLACKFARMERS _ The U.S. Department of Agriculture is
investigating whether black farmers in two Georgia counties were
improperly denied disaster assistance. But farmers who won a
settlement in a lawsuit against the government over other
discrimination issues say the disaster-aid problem exists in
virtually every county in Georgia and other states. The situation
may lead to another class-action lawsuit by black farmers against
the agriculture agency. (Judd, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HUNT-COUNTRY _ MIDDLEBURG, Va. _ The essence of Hunt Country was
captured on the Virginia license plate: POLO MOM. In this historic
piedmont in the shadows of the Blue Ridge Mountains, the scents of
money and manure have long mingled. (Dart, Cox News Service). WITH
PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   Moved Monday in (a) national and (l) lifestyle categories.
</P>
