<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-14 22:22 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7682 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r s BC-FBN-COWBOYSLINEBACKER     08-14 0631
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYSLINEBACKERS-TEX </SLUG>
 
COWBOYS LINEBACKERS KNOW NOTHING IS CERTAIN (For use by NYTimes
News Service clients) 
By JEFF CAPLAN 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   WICHITA FALLS, Texas _ The starters are etched in stone: Dexter
Coakley at weakside linebacker, Randall Godfrey patrols the middle
and Quentin Coryatt, whenever he gets healthy again, will tackle
the strong side.
</P>
<P>
   Dat Nguyen, the fearless fan favorite, is assured a spot as a
reserve.
</P>
<P>
   Then it gets sticky.
</P>
<P>
   For Darren Hambrick, Myron Smith, Nate Hemsley, Robert Thomas _
even throw in surprise TCU rookie free-agent Joe Phipps _ there is
nothing quite like realizing that three of them likely won't make
it to the Sept. 12 opener.
</P>
<P>
   ``You can't help but think about ... You become a unit, a family
in there,'' Coakley said. ``But you know everyone can't make the
squad.''
</P>
<P>
   Cowboys coaches are thrilled with the talented linebacker
overflow this training camp. In a reversal from recent camps, this
one is stocked with more quality candidates than Lake Wichita
yields catfish.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's going to be a hard decision to cut any of those
players,'' said Hemsley, a burgeoning special-teams player last
year until a fractured ankle in Week 3 ended his season.
</P>
<P>
   It all makes for some interesting and intense practice sesssions
among a group that shares similar characteristics.
</P>
<P>
   ``They're young, and they're fast,'' defensive coordinator Dave
Campo said. ``I really think this is the best group we have had in
long time as far as speed, the hungriness and the competitiveness
of this bunch. I really feel like it's going to be a real tough
deal at the end of it.''
</P>
<P>
   Inspired special-teams play and versatility to play other
positions will eventually separate team members from the NFL's
unemployed. Coach Chan Gailey said he will keep five to seven
linebackers on the roster. In recent years the Cowboys have gone
with the minimum of five and opted to bolster the defensive
backfield simply because of better special-teams players at the
position. Campo said that trend is quickly reversing as well.
</P>
<P>
   Not only is the quality of the players making the evaluation
process difficult, but injuries are also hampering things. Coryatt
hasn't practiced at full speed, and Hemsley is still undergoing
rehabilitation.
</P>
<P>
   ``In my mind,'' Hambrick said, ``all we can do is control what
we can control, and that's what we do on the field. You have to be
consistent. It's tough getting out there knowing it's your big
evaluation period.''
</P>
<P>
   Hambrick, entering his second NFL season, is the closest thing
to a lock outside of Nguyen. The second-round draft pick out of
South Carolina is aggressive and athletic, which showed in his
special-teams play last season when he finished second on the team
in special-teams tackles.
</P>
<P>
   Hemsley, if he can return to full strength, is the favorite to
nail down the sixth and likely final linebacker spot. He hopes to
impress enough to earn playing time on special defensive packages
such as nickel schemes.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're not just competing against each other as linebackers,
we're also competing against DBs and wide receivers for
\Rspecial-teams\S spots,'' Hemsley said. ``It's set who's going to
be starting; the other six guys or whatever it is have to go out
there and work.''
</P>
<P>
   Thomas, who recorded seven tackles in the exhibition opener
against Cleveland, is also clearly in the mix. He played on special
teams and on goal-line defenses last year, then played this spring
for the Rhein Fire of NFL Europe.
</P>
<P>
   Myron Smith, who was on the team last year but did not play, has
his work cut out, while Phipps is a long shot.
</P>
<P>
   ``This, by far, is one of the better units I've seen since I've
been here,'' Coakley said.
</P>
<P>
   The only question is who will remain.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
