<SLUG> BC-FBN-LYONSCOLUMN-TEX </SLUG>
 
PARCELLS' ACT CAN'T DISGUISE JETS (For use by NYTimes News Service
clients) 
By KEVIN LYONS 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   GREEN BAY, Wis. _ When we last saw Broadway Joe's Jets, they
were sad spectators to John Elway's conquering farewell at Mile
High Stadium in January, having squandered a 10-point lead in the
AFC Championship Game.
</P>
<P>
   Since then, the Jets, with some smart off-season acquisitions,
have done enough to make you think they'll make the AFC title game
again.
</P>
<P>
   And why stop there. How does a New York Jets-Minnesota Vikings
Super Bowl sound?
</P>
<P>
   Last night, in their first on-field action since the debacle in
Denver, the Jets starters looked like they were ready for the
season opener. Quarterback Vinny Testaverde, a poster boy for
reclamation projects that go right, led the Jets on two long
scoring drives against the Green Bay Packers' first-team defense.
The Jets first-team defense, meanwhile, scored a draw against the
Packers' first-team offense, allowing a Brett Favre touchdown pass
on the Packers' first preseason drive of the year, and then forcing
a Favre third-down incompletion on the Packers' next drive.
</P>
<P>
   Ah, but this is still the preseason. The tundra is not yet
frozen. The easy going summer two-a-days have yet to give way to
the pressure cooker Sundays of November and December.
</P>
<P>
   ``Who knows what this season holds _ I have no idea,'' said Jets
coach Bill Parcells, who is rumored among the New York media to be
in his last year as Jets head coach. ``There are things I like
about my team and several things I have a big degree of uncertainty
about. There are some ``big'' question marks and there is a
question of whether we can answer these question marks.''
</P>
<P>
   Parcells can poor-mouth his team with the best of them. But
don't let his coachspeak fool you. Mark this down: The Jets will
hold off the Dolphins and Bills to repeat as AFC Champions this
year. They can make their first Super Bowl appearance since
You-Know-Who's guarantee with a break or two.
</P>
<P>
   The key, of course, is Testaverde. He won the job from Glenn
Foley in Week 3 last year and finished with 29 touchdowns, seven
interceptions and a career best 101.6 passer rating. He didn't show
much rust last night. He led the Jets on an 87-yard drive that
ended with a field goal, and a 66-yard drive that concluded with
his 19-yard touchdown pass to newly acquired free agent tight end
Eric Green. Testaverde left the game after completing 11 of 13
passes for 147 yards _ including the touchdown pass _ and
committing no turnovers.
</P>
<P>
   ``From every Italian in New Jersey last year it was, `What you
get him for,'?'' Parcells said. ``Now, it's, `My man Vinny. That's
my man.' Yes, there is pressure on him this year. There is plenty
of pressure on him after what he did last year. But he's more
relaxed from the standpoint of knowing the system and the people
coaching him.''
</P>
<P>
   The Jets did not just stand pat after last year's breakthrough
season. Despite a talent base that already includes Testaverde,
running back Curtis Martin and wide receivers Keyshawn Johnson and
Wayne Chrebet, Parcells, who doubles as the club's general manager,
signed veteran free safety Steve Atwater, linebacker Roman Phifer,
and Green in the off-season. All will start in 1999.
</P>
<P>
   The club's only question mark, albeit a pretty big one, is in
the offensive line. Starting guards Matt O'Dwyer and Todd Burger
were not resigned. The starter on the right side is expected to be
rookie Randy Thomas. Three players are competing for the starting
position on the left _ second-year player Kerry Jenkins, who was a
backup tackle in 1998, rookie David Loverne, and rookie Ian
Beckles.
</P>
<P>
   ``There are a litany of things I'm concerned about,'' Parcells
poor-mouths. ``Now you can just slough them off as, `That's just
Bill.' But those problems, and how we do with them will probably
determine how far we go this year.''
</P>
<P>
   It says here they'll go pretty far. nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-14-99 2348EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
