<SLUG> BC-CLINTON-HOUSEHUNT-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CLINTONS TO GO HOUSE HUNTING IN NEW YORK'S WESTCHESTER COUNTY  
 (HLW) 
</HEADLINE>
   c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ In a sign that President Clinton and Hillary Rodham
Clinton are close to reaching a decision on where to live after
they leave the White House, the first couple planned to visit
Westchester County on Sunday to inspect houses to buy, some
associates of the Clintons said Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Until now, Mrs. Clinton, who is considering a race for the U.S.
Senate, has been doing the house hunting for the Clintons.
</P>
<P>
   That Clinton will, for the first time, join his wife on the
search means that they are close to making a decision about a home
purchase, the associates said.
</P>
<P>
   The Clintons are expected to fly into Westchester County Airport
and look at homes only in Westchester. On Wednesday, Mrs. Clinton
inspected a seven-bedroom, turn-of-the-century Colonial house in
Greenburgh, priced around $1.7 million. The house, in the town's
Edgemont section, is next to Scarsdale, one of the county's most
affluent communities.
</P>
<P>
   Associates of the Clintons would not say Saturday night what
other houses might be on their real-estate tour.
</P>
<P>
   Mrs. Clinton has come under increasing pressure by Democrats to
settle on a place to live in preparation for a race for the Senate
in New York, where she has not lived before. The first lady has
said that she and her husband would live in New York regardless of
whether she ran for the Senate.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
